Wikimedia Commons has media related to George Floyd protests in California.
There have been a series of protests in California related to the death of George Floyd on May 25, 2020 in Minneapolis while in police custody. On May 31, 2020, the California Department of Human Resources advised "all state departments with offices in downtown city areas" to close on June 1.[5]
